  "response": "Here are some ways to reduce excessive palm sweating (hyperhidrosis):\n\n1. Medical treatments:\n- Prescription antiperspirants\n- Botox injections\n- Prescription medications\n- Iontophoresis (electrical treatment)\n\n2. Over-the-counter solutions:\n- Antiperspirant hand lotions\n- Medicated hand wipes\n- Sweat-blocking creams\n\n3. Natural remedies:\n- Sage tea\n- Apple cider vinegar\n- Witch hazel\n- Black tea soaks\n\n4. Lifestyle changes:\n- Reduce caffeine intake\n- Manage stress\n- Stay hydrated\n- Use powder or cornstarch\n- Avoid spicy foods\n- Wear breathable gloves\n\n5. Advanced treatments:\n- Microwave therapy\n- Surgical options like sympathectomy\n\n6. Daily management:\n- Carry hand towels\n- Use oil-absorbing sheets\n- Keep hands cool\n- Wash hands frequently\n\nIf excessive sweating significantly impacts your life, consult a dermatologist for personalized advice and treatment options.",
